AB  - OBJECTIVE: To explore whether ambient magnetic fluctuations influence memory performance in artificial neural organisms. METHODS: Simulated agents were exposed to varying magnetic field patterns while completing pattern-recognition tasks. Performance metrics and error rates were recorded across experimental conditions. RESULTS: Moderate magnetic variability was associated with improved task performance, while extreme fluctuations reduced accuracy. CONCLUSION: Magnetic environmental factors may modulate cognitive efficiency in synthetic systems.
