AB  - OBJECTIVE: To assess whether microbial communities can adapt to synthetic gravity conditions in orbital bioreactors. METHODS: Mixed microbial cultures were cultivated under variable gravity simulations using rotating bioreactor systems. Growth rates and metabolic profiles were analyzed. RESULTS: Microbial populations displayed rapid adaptation and altered metabolic signatures under non-standard gravity conditions. CONCLUSION: Synthetic gravity environments can drive novel microbial evolutionary trajectories.
