AB  - OBJECTIVE: To determine whether exposure to algorithmically generated soundscapes affects plant growth dynamics. METHODS: Plants were exposed to procedurally generated acoustic patterns over a six-week period. Growth rate and leaf morphology were quantified. RESULTS: Certain sound patterns correlated with accelerated growth and altered structural traits. CONCLUSION: Algorithmic acoustic environments may influence biological development in plants.
